Written by Faith Erin Hicks (The Adventures of Superhero Girl, The Last of Us: American Dreams) and illustrated by Peter Wartman (Stonebreaker, Over the Wall) and Adele Matera, the same team behind the Imbalance trilogy.', 'A standalone comic in the Avatar: The Last Airbender universe, focusing on Toph Beifong, the iconic earthbender and metalbending inventor.', 2021, '1506717128', '9781506717128', 80, NULL, NULL, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/10482156-L.jpg', '/works/OL29259604W', NULL, 'Feb 16, 2021', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'avatar-faith-erin-hicks', 1, 'openlibrary', NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-17 23:32:29', '2026-03-23 04:22:05');
INSERT INTO books (id, title, description, summary, publication_year, isbn_10, isbn_13, pages, words, audio_length_minutes, cover_image_url, open_library_key, asin, publication_date, language, publisher, is_fiction, is_box_set, slug, cover_verified, cover_source, series_cover_url, needs_review, review_reason, visibility, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('bba24540-4f27-43d8-877d-687c91def996', 'Avatar', '**Aang and friends must join together once again as the four nations'' tenuous peace is threatened by an impasse between Fire Lord Zuko and Earth King Kuei!**

Aang and friends must join together once again as the four nations'' tenuous peace is threatened in an impasse between Fire Lord Zuko and Earth King Kuei! As the world heads toward another devastating war, Aang''s friendship with Zuko throws him into the middle of the conflict! Featuring annotations by Eisner Award-winning writer Gene Luen Yang (American Born Chinese) and artist Gurihiru (Thor and the Warriors Four), and a brand-new sketchbook, this is a story that Avatar fans need in an edition they will love!

Collects **Avatar: The Last Airbender: The Promise Parts 1-3**.', 'Aang and friends strive to prevent war as tensions rise between Fire Lord Zuko and Earth King Kuei in this thrilling Avatar graphic novel.', 2006, '1506708129', '9781506708126', 240, NULL, NULL, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/9832967-L.jpg', '/works/OL15416051W', NULL, 'Jun 16, 2020', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'avatar-michael-dante-dimartino', 1, 'openlibrary', NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-17 23:32:33', '2026-03-22 05:08:32');
